parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To pass through, spread (as a report). From dia and erchomai; to traverse.
Probably of foreign origin; Pisidia, a region of Asia Minor.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural

str2: A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From a compound of pas and pura; every-tribal, i.e. Heterogeneous; Pamphylia, a region of Asia Minor.
